fields.about: My name is Frank Campos. I am a student at the Nashville Software School and I am 39 years old. Originally from El Salvador, I have been living in the USA since 2006. I have two daughters, aged 12 and 9. I have hypothyroidism, and every six months I have to visit the doctor. I love to go to HardCore shows and right now I am learning Django and React. My favorite food is the pupusa. My mom's name is Lidia.

fields.pronunciation: /ɑː/- Open back unrounded vowel (commonly called "long 'a'" or "broad 'a'")
/ɒ/ - Open back rounded vowel (referred to as "short 'o'")
/ʌ/ - Open-mid back unrounded vowel (known as "caret" or "short 'u'")
/ɜː/ - Open-mid central unrounded vowel (referred to as "long 'er'" or "stressed schwa")
